The
practice
of
that
district
had
been
in
the
hands
of
Edward
Rowe,
the
son
of
Sir
William
Rowe,
the
Liverpool
consultant,
but
he
had
not
inherited
the
talents
of
his
father,
and
Dr.
Lana,
with
his
advantages
of
presence
and
of
